  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Rapid response to the humanitarian crisis caused by Nyiragongo Volcanic eruption in Nord Kivu province in the Democratic Republic of Congo</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to provide life-saving health assistance through reduction of morbidity and mortality related to health risks following the volcanic eruption in north Kivu. This WHO project provides: Cholera vaccination and access to medical care for affected populations through (i) early detection and active case finding and (ii) infection prevention and control measures. The project provides life-saving assistance to 132,802 people, including 37,477 women, 34,701 men, 66,625 children, and 20,818 people with disabilities.</narrative>
  </description>
